opular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":22,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Agnes Wycliff was born about 1360, in Breckland, Norfolk, England, her father, Wycliff, was 21 and her mother, Wycliff, was 21. She had at least 1 son with Thomas A Meade. She died about 1395, in her hometown, at the age of 37."},"et":{"about 1360–about 1395":"umbes 1360–umbes 1395","1360–1395":"1360–1395","1362–Male":"1362–Surnud","1387–1455":"1387–1455","1340–Male":"1340–Surnud","1340–Female":"1340–Surnud","about 1360":"umbes 1360","1455":"1455","Abt 1387":"umbes 1387","1387":"1387","1340":"1340","1362":"1362","1395":"1395","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","about 1395":"umbes 1395","Breckland, Norfolk, England":"Breckland, Norfolk, England","Mead's Place, Wraxal, Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1360–about 1395":"noin 1360–noin 1395","1360–1395":"1360–1395","1362–Male":"1362–Kuollut","1387–1455":"1387–1455","1340–Male":"1340–Kuollut","1340–Female":"1340–Kuollut","about 1360":"noin 1360","1455":"1455","Abt 1387":"noin 1387","1387":"1387","1340":"1340","1362":"1362","1395":"1395","1382":"1382","1360":"1360","about 1395":"noin 1395","Breckland, Norfolk, England":"Breckland, Norfolk, England","Mead's Place, Wraxal, Gloucestershire, England":"Gloucestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1360–about 1395":"environ 1360–environ 1395","1360–1395":"1360–1395","1362–Male":"1362–Décédé","1387–1455":"1387–1455","1340–Male":"1340–Décédé","1340–Female":"1340–Décédée","